title: You submit a file 1 in Google Classroom, but then unsubmit it because it’s a wrong file. Later you submit the correct file instead. Can a teacher still open the 1st file that you unsubmitted? - Quora

response.answer_text: Theoretically they could. In practice, they would only open up the last file and do the grading based on your latest version. If that latest version is late, you’ll get the penalty for being late which could sometimes mean that you’d get less points than if the older submission which was on time was considered.
